                <!-- Key Concepts -->
                <div class="concepts-section">
                    <h2 class="section-title">Key Concepts</h2>
                    <div class="concepts-grid">
                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h3>üåä Surface Tension</h3>
                            <p>
                                In microgravity, surface tension becomes the dominant force. Water molecules pull together, 
                                forming perfect spheres - the shape with minimal surface area.
                            </p>
                            <div class="concept-example">
                                <strong>Example:</strong> Astronauts can create floating water spheres that wobble like jelly!
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h3>üî• Marangoni Effect</h3>
                            <p>
                                Temperature differences create surface tension gradients, causing fluid flow from warm to cool regions. 
                                This drives convection in space where gravity can't.
                            </p>
                            <div class="concept-example">
                                <strong>Example:</strong> Hot spots cause fluid circulation even without gravity.
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h3>‚ö´ Capillary Action</h3>
                            <p>
                                Liquids naturally climb up narrow spaces due to adhesion and surface tension. 
                                In space, this effect is amplified without gravity pulling fluids down.
                            </p>
                            <div class="concept-example">
                                <strong>Example:</strong> ISS water systems use capillary action for fluid management.
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="concept-card">
                            <h3>üß¨ Colloid Behavior</h3>
                            <p>
                                Suspended particles in fluids naturally organize themselves without gravity's interference, 
                                enabling study of self-assembly and crystal formation.
                            </p>
                            <div class="concept-example">
                                <strong>Example:</strong> Perfect protein crystals grown for pharmaceutical research.
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

